{"TopicId":153936,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Dust storm mod?","CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T01:57:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T01:57:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi guys!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that adds dust storm to planets? They don\u0027t have to kill/break anything, just makes it hard to see and such.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T02:41:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe this can be simulated using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E by putting clouds at ground level. Try \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E or SVE and see if there are dust clouds on Duna. If not, it\u0027s probably not exorbitantly hard to add some.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T06:37:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kRQzkJS.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kRQzkJS.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E clouds, yes; not too far from the infamous \u003Cem\u003EMinmus Fog\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T14:46:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! Using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E, does the clouds come and go randomly, or do I set the time they appear/disappear? (I prefer randomized)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}